$ Excel Popup: Format Cells

The *format cells* popup can be opened with the `ctrl+shift+f` → Microsoft/Office/Excel#excel-key-shortcut[shortcut] or
on the Ribbon going to → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Home/Cells/Format/Protection[Home -> cells -> Format -> Protection] -> Format Cells

{ Number #xls-format-cells-number

  Categories
    • General
    • Number
    • Currency
    • Accounting
    • Date
    • Time
    • Percentage
    • Fraction
    • Scientific
    • Text
    • Special
    • Custom

  The *Alignment tab* can be opened directly using the *thingy* at the bottem right corner of → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Home/Number[Home -> Number] Ribbon group.
}
{ Alignment #xls-format-cells-alignment

  Text alignment:
    • Horizontal
    • Vertical
    • Indent

  Text control
    • Wrap text
    • Shrink to fit
    • Merge cells

  Right-to-left
    • Text direction

  Orientation

  The *Alignment tab* can be opened directly using the *thingy* at the bottem right corner of → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Home/Alignment[Home -> Alignment] Ribbon group.

}
{ Font #xls-format-cells-font

  Choose
    • Font
    • Font style (regular, italic, bold, bold-italic)
    • Size
    • Underline
    • Color
    • Normal font (yes/no)
    • Effects (strikethrough, superscript, subscript)

  The *Font tab* can be opened directly using the *thingy* at the bottem right corner of → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Home/Font[Home -> Font] Ribbon group.

}
{ Border

  Line
    • Style
    • Color

  Allows to choose from presets

}
{ Fill

  Choose
    • Background color
    • Pattern color
    • Pattern style
    • Fill effects
    • More colors

}
{ Protection #xls-format-cells-protection

  Tick or untick
    • Locked
    • Hidden (formulas?)
    
  Locking cells or hiding formulas has no effect until the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet is protected
 (→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Review/Protect/Protect-Sheet[Review -> Change -> Protect Sheet])

}
